}
<!-- Display the structure diagram with a link to download the PDF's thereof -->

<br />
<div class="row">
    <div class="col">
        <h2>Class structure diagram</h2>
        <p>
            The class structure diagram for the webapp is relatively straightforward.
            The abstract class 'User' is parent to three subclasses, namely 'Student', 'Educator' and 'Administrator'.
        </p>
        <p>
            The child classes inherit all attributes of the parent class. Only the Educator subclass makes use of the 'worksContributed' virtual method.
            Both the Educator and Student subclasses make use of the 'Rating' abstract method. The method of determining the ratings varies, however.
            Educators are rated based on the amount of material they have uploaded, and students are rated based on the number of materials they
            have downloaded. The ratings are represented by an integer that increases indefinitley.
        </p>
        <p>
            The administrator alone has a 'Salary' attribute. The educator alone has the 'Institution', 'contributions' and 'contributionCount' attributes.
            The student alone has the 'School' and 'downloads' attributes.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
        <img src="~/Resources/Other_Images/Diagrams/Class_diagram_rev2.0.drawio.png" />
    </div>
</div>

<hr />

<!-- Make this a carousel of the UC diagrams with links to download the PDF's thereof -->
